types-metadata.jsonThe `@types/react-virtualized` package is providing the old v4 types that compete with my custom.d.ts declaration. The old types have `CellMeasurer` with `cellRenderer`, `columnCount`, `rowCount` as required props. My `declare module 'react-virtualized'` in custom.d.ts should override it, but the `@types/react-virtualized` package uses a different format (triple-slash reference and `declare module`).

Let me check if the old types are taking precedence:
