    interface CellMeasurerProps {
    export class CellMeasurer extends React.Component<CellMeasurerProps, {}> { }The old `@types/react-virtualized` declares `CellMeasurer` with the old API inside `declare module "react-virtualized"`, and my `custom.d.ts` also declares `module 'react-virtualized'`. Both are ambient module declarations, so they get merged — the old `CellMeasurerProps` with `cellRenderer`, `columnCount`, `rowCount` required takes precedence for the class constructor overloads.

