Ran all test suites.The `TextEncoder` from `util` is also `undefined` because the import from `util` happens in the same module scope as the `react-dom` import (via enzyme adapter). The `import` statement is hoisted by the module system before the assignment. The `TextEncoder` needs to be defined before any module imports. Let me use a separate setup file that runs before the imports:
  ────────────────────────────────────────
  ▸ write
    path jest-polyfills.js
    content: // Polyfill TextEncoder/TextDecoder for jsdom environment (required by React 18)
const { TextEncoder, TextDecoder } = require('util');

if (typeof global.TextEncoder === 'undefined') {
  global.TextEncoder = TextEncoder;
}
if (typeof global.TextDecoder === 'undefined') {
  global.TextDecoder = TextDecoder;
}


